{
  "texts": [
    "We will discuss the corresponding power spectra and propagators in the following section.",
    "Mass parameter comparisonAs emphasised in [88], in the CCM case the masses of the fields have a wider range as they are not constrained by the Higuchi bound.",
    "For comparison, in figure 4 we show the distribution JHEP05(2024)196 of the dimensionless mass parameter on the complex plane for light/heavy fields in both the CCM and the CC scenarios.",
    "From (2.13) we see that for light fields in the CCM scenario ν cannot exceed the massless boundary of ν = 3/2, while for heavy fields we can keep increasing the mass to keep increasing the value of Im ν.",
    "Similarly, in the CC scenario we see from (2.41) that Im ν S continues to increase as we increase the mass while in the principle series."
  ]
}